For sale is a very Mosin Nagant 91/30 refurb. I'm refocusing / slimming my collection and sadly this one has to go. Made in 1942 at the Izhevsk arms factory this rifle likely saw serious service during the Great Patriotic War. postcontent: This is probably the most versitile rifle in the world. It can do everything from plink, pick off a white tail, all the way op to knocking down Cape Buffalo. Plinking?? Absolutely!
